commentPostTextItems.html: Well that's it finished after a rain delayed second innings. Canada never really got going and they were always miles behind the DL par score after loosing several early wickets. Scotland's total was always safe but they were boosted by another half-century from the in form Berrington and a superb 89* from Neil McCallum.

Elsewhere the Netherlands comprehensively beat Kenya and the Ireland v Afghanistan game will resume tomorrow due to rain. The groundstaff here at Amstelveen did a good job to get the pitch playable but the last five overs did little to change to results as Canada went down swinging. Do join us soon for all the other World Cricket League games live ball-by-ball commentary but for now from me Callum Stewart it's goodbye.
Man of the Match award - Neil McCallum for his 89*
